The South African Reserve Bank said
it appointed Zanele Mavuso Mbatha as head of its financial
markets department from January, replacing Roelf du Plooy, who
will retire at the end of April.  Andre Bezuidenhout was named head of risk management and
compliance, a newly created department, from next month while
Rashad Cassim was appointed head of the bankâ€™s research
department from March, the Pretoria-based central bank said in a
